/Min Huang","target":"Author/Min Huang","line":89},{"title":"Author/Min Huang","target":"Author/Min Huang","line":90},{"title":"Author/Shu-Feng Zhou","target":"Author/Shu-Feng Zhou","line":91},{"title":"Author/Shu-Feng Zhou","target":"Author/Shu-Feng Zhou","line":92},{"title":"PDF","target":"biblib/tang_randomized_2005/tang_randomized_2005.pdf","line":94}],"metadata":{"id":"tang_randomized_2005","type":"article-journal","title":"A randomized, double-blind and placebo-controlled study of a Ganoderma lucidum polysaccharide extract in neurasthenia.","issued":{"date-parts":[[2005]]},"DOI":"10.1089/jmf.2005.8.53","container-title":"Journal of Medicinal Food","abstract":"Ganoderma lucidum has been widely used to treat various diseases, including cancer, diabetes, and neurasthenia in many Asian countries. This randomized, double-blind, placebo-controlled parallel study aimed to investigate the efficacy and safety of a polysaccharide extract of G. lucidum (Ganopoly) in Chinese patients with neurasthenia. One hundred thirty-two patients with neurasthenia according to the diagnosis criteria of the 10th International Classification of Diseases were included in this study. Written consents were obtained from the patients, and the study was conducted in accordance with Good Clinical Practice guidelines. Patients were randomized to receive Ganopoly or placebo orally at 1,800 mg three times a day for 8 weeks. Efficacy assessments comprised the Clinical Global Impression (CGI) improvement of severity scale and the Visual Analogues Scales for the sense of fatigue and well-being. In 123 assessable patients in two treatment groups at the end of the study, Ganopoly treatment for 8 week...","tags":["#literature_note"],"author":[{"family":"Tang","given":"Wenbo","literal":""},{"family":"Tang","given":"Wenbo","literal":""},{"family":"Gao","given":"Yihuai","literal":""},{"family":"Gao","given":"Yihuai","literal":""},{"family":"Chen","given":"Guoliang","literal":""},{"family":"Chen","given":"Guoliang","literal":""},{"family":"He","given":"Guangming","literal":""},{"family":"Gao","given":"He","literal":""},{"family":"Dai","given":"Xihu","literal":""},{"family":"Dai","given":"Xihu","literal":""},{"family":"Ye","given":"Jinxian","literal":""},{"family":"Ye","given":"Jinxian","literal":""},{"family":"Chan","given":"Eli","literal":""},{"family":"Chan","given":"Eli","literal":""},{"family":"Huang","given":"Min","literal":""},{"family":"Huang","given":"Min","literal":""},{"family":"Zhou","given":"Shu-Feng","literal":""},{"family":"Zhou","given":"Shu-Feng","literal":""}],"citation-key":"tang_randomized_2005","year":"2005","dateCreated":"2026-03-31","reading-status":"to-read","aliases":["A randomized, double-blind and placebo-controlled study of a Ganoderma lucidum polysaccharide extract in neurasthenia."],"author-links":["[[Author/Wenbo Tang]]","[[Author/Wenbo Tang]]","[[Author/Yihuai Gao]]","[[Author/Yihuai Gao]]","[[Author/Guoliang Chen]]","[[Author/Guoliang Chen]]","[[Author/Guangming He]]","[[Author/He Gao]]","[[Author/Xihu Dai]]","[[Author/Xihu Dai]]","[[Author/Jinxian Ye]]","[[Author/Jinxian Ye]]","[[Author/Eli Chan]]","[[Author/Eli Chan]]","[[Author/Min Huang]]","[[Author/Min Huang]]","[[Author/Shu-Feng Zhou]]","[[Author/Shu-Feng Zhou]]"],"attachment":["[[biblib/tang_randomized_2005/tang_randomized_2005.pdf|PDF]]"],"related":[[]]},"task_lines":[],"tasks":{},"codeblock_ranges":[],"last_embed":{"hash":"1r7sxl4","at":1774951886863}},"smart_blocks:Research/@tang_randomized_2005.md#---frontmatter---": {"path":null,"embeddings":{"TaylorAI/bge-micro-v2":{"vec":[-0.04890955,0.00458937,0.06629508,-0.01832158,0.0477881,0.01314995,0.04141805,0.02260949,-0.02948698,-0.01851608,0.0368294,-0.03451986,0.02016686,0.0380602,-0.00690045,-0.00923504,0.03161528,-0.02313759,-0.07900777,0.00984297,0.06677773,-0.10298759,0.04577406,0.00046155,0.05718965,0.05584863,0.00536471,-0.03250593,-0.03380895,-0.21137057,-0.01645397,-0.00978804,-0.01404283,-0.03863933,-0.05994635,-0.021